definitions: a burrowing ground squirrel with cheek pouches and light and dark stripes running down the body, found in North America and northern Eurasia.

notes.text: Genus Tamias, family Sciuridae: many species, including the eastern chipmunk (T. striatus), common in the eastern US

shortDefinitions: burrowing ground squirrel with cheek pouches and light and dark stripes running down body, found in North America
